<p>You see the other person for who they really are, not for what they represent or signify. In this relationships, there is a willingness to understand the other person on a deeper level than your immediate judgements, assumptions and stereotypes that you bring to the relationship.</p>

<h1 id="i-it-relationship">I-It relationship</h1>

<p>You view the other person more as a â€˜thingâ€™ than a human being with a story and individual needs. In and I-it relationship you assume you know the other person, without needing to take time to develop a close and mutual relationship with them.</p>
